Frank,

  I&#39;m new to the whole paranormal investigation thing.
I did the mod in a radio shack radio and am not sure
of what I&#39;m getting. I&#39;ve recorded somethings and had
other people listen to them. I don&#39;t tell them what I
think it says. Sometimes they hear things I didn&#39;t
hear. Sometimes they hear what I believed I did hear.
I do log time dates location and moon cycles. weather
conditions...And what I hear....

   What is needed in my own opinion. Is the community
needs to stop all the childish infighting and be
honest with eachother. I think these methods do have
potiential to be an asset to paranormal investigation.
I feel that more research needs to be done and
standards need to be set. The only way this is going
to happen is if we all work together. Putting our
personal feelings and beliefs aside. 

  I&#39;m stepping down from my soap box now. Thank you
Frank for allowing me to join the group. I would like
to get a Real Box so I can further contribute to this
quest for knowledge......David
